<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  com.firstmate.poller - launchd LaunchAgent for the workflow-paradigm board /
  merge / stall poller (bin/fm-poll.sh).

  DO NOT LOAD THIS PLIST YET.

  Loading it is the human-verified poller cutover step, run once, after the
  paradigm PR merges and only when David has confirmed the synthetic startup
  wake and one real board thread + action both arrive through the durable wake
  queue. Loading it now would run a second board poller alongside the still-live
  escape-hatch watcher (bin/fm-watch.sh) and double-deliver every board event.
  The old watcher carries the pollers until this cutover; it is never left
  disarmed before this is loaded.

  Before loading, replace the two placeholders below with real absolute paths
  (launchd does not expand ~ or environment variables in these fields):
    __FM_ROOT__  ->  the absolute firstmate repo path, e.g. /Users/dq4443/dev/personal/firstmate
    __FM_HOME__  ->  the operational home (usually the same as __FM_ROOT__)

  Then, as the human cutover step (do not let a session run this):
    cp launchd/com.firstmate.poller.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
    launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.firstmate.poller.plist
    launchctl list com.firstmate.poller          # confirm it is loaded
  Then confirm the synthetic startup wake drains, run the one-time board test,
  and only then disarm bin/fm-watch.sh. KeepAlive + ThrottleInterval mean a
  kill -9 of the poller is restarted by launchd within the throttle window;
  verify that too.

  Same cutover, wire the PreToolUse write fence (bin/fm-write-fence.sh). It is
  deliberately NOT in tracked .claude/settings.json (this is a shared-template
  repo; a fresh clone must not silently broaden every user's fence). Add it to
  the home's local .claude/settings.local.json as a PreToolUse hook on
  Edit|Write|NotebookEdit, and drop the retired .claude/block-html-edits.sh
  reference at the same time:
    "PreToolUse": [ { "matcher": "Edit|Write|NotebookEdit",
      "hooks": [ { "type": "command",
        "command": "\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\"/bin/fm-write-fence.sh" } ] } ]
  Then confirm a write into a projects/ clone or ~/dev/work checkout is blocked
  and a write into an isolated worktree is allowed (AGENTS.md prime rule 2).
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>Label</key>
  <string>com.firstmate.poller</string>

  <key>ProgramArguments</key>
  <array>
    <string>/bin/bash</string>
    <string>__FM_ROOT__/bin/fm-poll.sh</string>
  </array>

  <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
  <dict>
    <key>FM_HOME</key>
    <string>__FM_HOME__</string>
  </dict>

  <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
  <string>__FM_ROOT__</string>

  <key>RunAtLoad</key>
  <true/>

  <key>KeepAlive</key>
  <true/>

  <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
  <integer>10</integer>

  <key>ProcessType</key>
  <string>Background</string>

  <key>StandardOutPath</key>
  <string>__FM_HOME__/state/poller.log</string>

  <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
  <string>__FM_HOME__/state/poller.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
